  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Jamieson-Fausset-Brown Bible Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "8. no man—literally, \"no one of men\": neither can a man control his neighbor's, nor even his own tongue. Hence the truth of Jas 3:2 appears.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "unruly evil—The Greek, implies that it is at once restless and incapable of restraint. Nay, though nature has hedged it in with a double barrier of the lips and teeth, it bursts from its barriers to assail and ruin men [Estius].",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "deadly—literally, \"death-bearing.\"",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  },
